<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB9C916FF62F885FAB0F855" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB9C916FF62F885FAB0F855" blockId="24.[151,1437,1663,2014]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FF62F885FECCF8EA" bold="true" box="[199,322,1807,1833]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB9C916FE0AF89AFDCCF8E9" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[431,578,1808,1834]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuyapichis" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FE0AF89AFDCCF8E9" box="[431,578,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. yuyapichis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FDE2F89AFD37F8E9" bold="true" box="[583,697,1808,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFB9C916FDE2F89AFD37F8E9" box="[583,697,1808,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB9C916FC2DF89AFC67F8E9" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[904,1001,1808,1834]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaiabi" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FC2DF89AFC67F8E9" box="[904,1001,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. kaiabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FC4BF89AFBEEF8E9" bold="true" box="[1006,1120,1808,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFB9C916FC4BF89AFBEEF8E9" box="[1006,1120,1808,1834]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB9C916FBC8F89AFB62F8E9" box="[1133,1260,1807,1834]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[171,1406,196,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[159,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Sadala kaiabi spec. nov. 13–15 Male (IBSP 246434, holotype), left palp (13 prolateral, 14 ventral, 15 retrolateral); 16–18 Female (IBSP 233316, paratype) (16 epigyne, 17 vulva, 18 schematic course of internal ducts system). C—conductor; CO—copulatory opening; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP— triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550209/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 13–15</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB9C916FA8CF89AFA13F8EA" authorityName="Simon IBSP" authorityYear="1880" box="[1321,1437,1808,1834]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punicea">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FA8CF89AFA13F8EA" box="[1321,1437,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. punicea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB9C916FF3AF8BEFE90F88D" box="[159,286,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–50" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,196,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[173,1414,181,1843]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 45–50. Sadala punicea Simon 45–47 Male (IBSP 9361), left palp (45 prolateral, 46 ventral, 47 retrolateral); 28–50. Female (IBSP 7362) (48 epigyne, 49 vulva, 50 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum; TP—triangular projection. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550229/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 45–47</figureCitation>
) by the palps with embolus arising from tegulum at 4 o’clock position (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB9C916FB9CF8BEFB03F88D" box="[1081,1165,1844,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–85" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,463,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-136@25.[153,1434,453,1734]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 83–85. Sadala yuyapichis spec. nov., male (MUSM, holotype), left palp (83 prolateral, 84 ventral 85 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm. C—conductor; E–embolus; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550251/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from both species by the embolus base with a retrolateral swing, extending beyond retrocymbial margin (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB9C916FAE7F8D2FA1AF8B1" box="[1346,1428,1880,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–85" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionTargetBox="[164,1419,463,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-136@25.[153,1434,453,1734]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 83–85. Sadala yuyapichis spec. nov., male (MUSM, holotype), left palp (83 prolateral, 84 ventral 85 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm. C—conductor; E–embolus; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550251/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
) (not extending beyond retrocymbial margin in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB9C916FD06F8F6FC8BF855" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[675,773,1916,1942]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaiabi" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FD06F8F6FC8BF855" box="[675,773,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. kaiabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FCA9F8F6FCF0F855" bold="true" box="[780,894,1916,1942]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFB9C916FCA9F8F6FCF0F855" box="[780,894,1916,1942]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB9C916FC10F8F6FBA4F856" authorityName="Simon IBSP" authorityYear="1880" box="[949,1066,1916,1942]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punicea">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FC10F8F6FBA4F856" box="[949,1066,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">S. punicea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB9C917FF62F815FA85FE4A" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB9C917FF62F815FDD9FE82" blockId="24.[151,1437,1663,2014]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,150,429]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB9C916FF62F815FDA2F87A" bold="true" box="[199,556,1951,1978]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFB9C916FE14F815FD91F87A" box="[433,543,1951,1977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 13.9. Prosoma: 6.6 long, 6.4 wide. Opisthosoma: 7.0 long, 4.3 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.55, 0.46, 0.35, 0.45; interdistances: 0.30, 0.07, 0.55, 0.56, 0.27, 0.15. Legs: I: 35.5 (9.9, 3.5, 9.2, 10.3, 2.6); II: 37.8 (10.6, 3.6, 10.1, 10.8, 2.7); III: 26.9 (8.3, 3.0, 6.5, 7.1, 2.0); IV: 29.8 (9.0, 2.7, 7.4, 8.4, 2.3). Spination follows the generic pattern except tibia I: d1-0-1; tibia II: d0-0-1. Palp: PTA triangular, as wide as long; RTA two times longer than wide, slightly rounded at tip (in ventral view); subtegulum visible prolaterally in ventral view; tegulum roughly rectangular; conductor four times longer than wide, surpassing anterior margin of alveolus by half its length (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB8C917FE62FEADFDC4FE82" box="[455,586,295,321]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 83–85" captionStart-1="FIGURES 86–88" captionStartId-0="25.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionStartId-1="26.[151,264,1233,1257]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1419,463,1720]" captionTargetBox-1="[171,1409,202,1198]" captionTargetId-0="figure-136@25.[153,1434,453,1734]" captionTargetId-1="figure-23@26.[156,1430,181,1209]" captionTargetPageId-0="25" captionTargetPageId-1="26" captionText-0="FIGURES 83–85. Sadala yuyapichis spec. nov., male (MUSM, holotype), left palp (83 prolateral, 84 ventral 85 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm. C—conductor; E–embolus; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 86–88. Sadala yuyapichis spec. nov., male (MUSM, holotype), left palp (86 prolateral, 87 ventral, 88 retrolateral). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550251" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550255" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6550251/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6550255/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 83–88</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB8C917FF62FEC1FE2BFEA6" blockId="25.[151,1436,150,429]" box="[199,421,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB8C917FF62FEC1FEA6FEA6" bold="true" box="[199,296,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Female:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB8C917FF62FEE4FA85FE4A" blockId="25.[151,1436,150,429]" box="[199,1291,366,393]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB8C917FF62FEE4FEB1FE4B" bold="true" box="[199,319,366,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n = 2): total length 13.9–14.9; prosoma length 6.5–6.6; femur I length 9.5–9.9.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB8C917FF62FE18FCD2FE6E" box="[199,860,402,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB8C917FF62FE18FCD2FE6E" blockId="25.[151,1436,150,429]" box="[199,860,402,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB8C917FF62FE18FEEFFE6F" bold="true" box="[199,353,402,428]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFB8C917FDC5FE19FD1EFE6E" box="[608,656,403,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB8C917FD5EFE19FCC1FE6E" box="[763,847,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–90" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 89–90. Distribution maps for Sadala spp. 89 S. tabatinga spec. nov., S. velox Simon, S. nanay spec. nov., S. punicea Simon 90 S. rufa (Keyserling), S. kaiabi spec. nov., S. keyserlingi Simon, S. nigristernis Simon, S. yuyapichis spec. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550257/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
